      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA generic pump hemolysis benchmark comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA experimental data across five operating points. Mean relative error 8.3%; RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all assessed conditions. NOTE: near-wall turbulence closure in high-shear impeller tip regions was identified as an area where the k-omega SST model may underestimate shear stress by up to 12% in edge cases not fully covered by the benchmark dataset. This limitation is acknowledged but the assessment proceeds without a documented explanation of why the associated residual risk is acceptable for the CPB COU."
