    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 requirements for MRL 2. The CFD model is accepted as sufficiently credible to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. A limitation was identified in the near-wall turbulence modelling for high-shear impeller tip regions, where the k-omega SST closure may underestimate local shear stress in edge cases not fully covered by the benchmark dataset; the residual risk associated with this limitation is considered acceptable.",
